wikipedia_page.main: Charles Harold Williams (23 June 1887 – 15 December 1971) was a British track and field athlete who competed in the 1908 Summer Olympics. He was born in Wolverhampton and died in Malvern, Worcestershire. In 1908 he finished eleventh in the long jump event.
